    "#### Question 4c\n",
    "Let $\\sigma(x) = \\dfrac{1}{1+e^{-x}}$. Show that $\\sigma(-x) = 1 - \\sigma(x)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "<!--\n",
    "BEGIN QUESTION\n",
    "name: q4c\n",
    "manual: true\n",
    "points: 2\n",
    "-->\n",
    "<!-- EXPORT TO PDF -->"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "nbgrader": {
     "grade": true,
     "grade_id": "question-4e-a-answer",
     "locked": false,
     "points": 2,
     "schema_version": 2,
     "solution": true
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "**SOLUTION:**  $$\\sigma(x) = \\dfrac{1}{1+e^{-x}} = \\dfrac{e^x}{e^x+1}$$\n",
    "\t\t\t\t$$\\sigma(-x) \n",
    "\t\t\t\t= \\dfrac{e^{-x}}{e^{-x}+1}\n",
    "\t\t\t\t= \\dfrac{e^{-x} + 1 - 1}{1 + e^{-x}}\n",
    "\t\t\t\t= \\dfrac{1 + e^{-x}}{1 + e^{-x}} - \\dfrac{1}{1 + e^{-x}}\n",
    "\t\t\t\t= 1- \\sigma(x)\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "deletable": false,
    "editable": false,
    "nbgrader": {
